Sentencas: A novel electrode architecture consisting in alternating layers of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) and Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (CGO) is prepared for the first time by spray-pyrolysis deposition and investigated as cathode material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: A novel multilaminated composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cathodes with different number of LSCF/CGO bilayers (N = 0, 3 and 5) are prepared and characterized.
Titulo: A novel multilaminated composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The multilaminated cathodes are highly porous with connected vertical channels and display an unusual undulated morphology, which increases the contact area between CGO and LSCF materials.
Titulo: A novel multilaminated composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction activity has been investigated by impedance spectroscopy, obtaining improved values of polarization resistance as the number of bilayers increases due to extended three-phase-boundary (TPB) length for the oxygen reduction reactions.
Titulo: A novel multilaminated composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
